1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,392
If you want to send your friend a message that

2
00:00:02,492 --> 00:00:04,940
is impossible for anyone else to read, do this.

3
00:00:05,300 --> 00:00:07,936
Start by making a truly random digit code.

4
00:00:08,036 --> 00:00:10,480
You could use dice and a table like this one.

5
00:00:11,036 --> 00:00:13,576
This code is the key you can only use once.

6
00:00:14,736 --> 00:00:17,756
You and your friend should memorize or safely store this.

7
00:00:17,856 --> 00:00:19,838
When you want to send a message to your

8
00:00:19,938 --> 00:00:22,508
friend, first turn your message into a digit code.

9
00:00:22,608 --> 00:00:25,340
You could use a straddling checkerboard to do this.

10
00:00:25,608 --> 00:00:27,959
Then subtract each digit in your key from a

11
00:00:28,059 --> 00:00:30,524
digit in the same position from your message.

12
00:00:32,008 --> 00:00:33,831
If the key digit is more than the

13
00:00:33,931 --> 00:00:36,396
message digit, add ten to the message digit.

14
00:00:38,408 --> 00:00:41,956
Then send the digits you get from the subtractions to your friend.

15
00:00:44,908 --> 00:00:48,460
If you receive a message like this from your friend, add back each

16
00:00:48,560 --> 00:00:52,224
digit from the key into what they sent. Do not carry between digits.

17
00:00:52,608 --> 00:00:56,204
Then you can turn the digit code back into a message you can read.

18
00:00:56,304 --> 00:00:58,208
Make sure the key is longer than or

19
00:00:58,308 --> 00:01:00,212
equal to the code from the message.

20
00:01:00,312 --> 00:01:02,948
Then the message will be just as secret as the key.

